"pedv---00000999-20180322-155044"/><CodeA name="nodelevel" value="0"/></CodeI></Code><Code value="asiaz"><CodeD index="no" lang="en">Asia</CodeD><CodeI org="expansion" action="add"><CodeA name="db" value="pedv---00000999-20180322-155044"/><CodeA name="root" value="re:singp"/></CodeI><CodeI org="validation" action="add"><CodeA name="db" value="pedv---00000999-20180322-155044"/><CodeA name="status" value="active"/></CodeI><CodeI org="hierarchy" action="add"><CodeA name="db" value="pedv---00000999-20180322-155044"/><CodeA name="nodelevel" value="0"/></CodeI></Code><Code value="seasiaz"><CodeD index="no" lang="en">Southeast Asia</CodeD><CodeI org="expansion" action="add"><CodeA name="db" value="pedv---00000999-20180322-155044"/><CodeA name="root" value="re:singp"/></CodeI><CodeI org="validation" action="add"><CodeA name="db" value="pedv---00000999-20180322-155044"/><CodeA name="status" value="active"/></CodeI><CodeI org="hierarchy" action="add"><CodeA name="db" value="pedv---00000999-20180322-155044"/><CodeA name="nodelevel" value="1"/></CodeI></Code></CSet></CodeSets></MetadataPT><ArchiveDoc xml:space="preserve"><Article markup="pp0" lang="en" index="field"><HandL fid="hlp"><Title fid="hl"><SectionName fid="se" index="field">Top of the News</SectionName><ColumnName fid="clm" index="field"></ColumnName><Headline fid="hd"><Para lang="en">Why It Matters; Easing stress of P1 registration</Para></Headline></Title><LeadPara fid="lp"><Para>For years, many parents had to go through the nerve-racking experience of balloting for a Primary 1 place in a school of their choice, in a process that has been likened to drawing Toto numbers.</Para><Para>When there are more children applying to a school than the number of places available, each child would be given a numbered ping-pong ball, which is then placed in a rotating cage.</Para></LeadPara></HandL><TailParas fid="td"><Para>Parents, sitting in a hall or a room of the school, would then hold their collective breath as school officials call out the numbers, one by painful one.</Para><Para>Cheers would quickly be drowned out by tears as the number of balls starts to dwindle.</Para><Para>But from this year's Primary 1 registration exercise, which starts in late June, this process will be replaced by computerised balloting handled centrally by the Ministry of Education - to the relief of parents.</Para><Para>Instead of having to watch the balloting up close and in person, parents will receive a text message notifying them of the results on the same day.</Para><Para>This will help to free up resources like school staff for other matters, and make school registration more efficient.</Para><Para>It will also be less of a hassle for parents, as they do not have to travel to the schools.</Para><Para>Tweaking this administrative part of the Primary 1 registration exercise could do more than streamline the whole process, say parents.</Para><Para>Yes, balloting remains. And with it, the stress of anticipation.</Para><Para>But parents say that by having some privacy during the process - like the way postings to secondary school or junior college are done - there will be less pressure from competing for a spot.</Para><Para>And, away from a room full of other anxious parents, they know there is a smaller chance of them being influenced into reacting publicly.</Para></TailParas><Byline fid="by" index="field">Amelia Teng </Byline><Credit fid="cr" index="field"></Credit><Contact fid="ct" index="field"></Contact><Notes fid="rf" index="field"></Notes><Art fid="art" index="field"></Art><Copyright fid="cy" index="field">(c) 2018 Singapore Press Holdings Limited </Copyright></Article></ArchiveDoc><AdocTOC adoctype="article"><Item size="0" ref="distdoc:archive/ArchiveDoc::Article" type="arttext"></Item><Item size="0" ref="distdoc:archive/InvertText" type="invtext"></Item></AdocTOC></DistDoc>

